status_message:
"Music gets everyone together, irrespective of their background. It unites people."
What would you want to convey through your music?  
"Live and let live."

"There's indiscipline in the society, here."
"Your take on that?"
"Any kind of work shouldn't be considered small, one should do it with full dedication."

"I'm a dancer, I love to create stuff." 
Would you say something about Delhi?
"Delhi's about variety, I connect myself with Delhi".

"Patna se yahan ka safar tha to bahut mushkil par ab do saal bad yeh jaga ghar hi lagne lagi hai. Kaam bhi thik hai aur log bhi, yahi pe manager ki naukri mil jae usi ke lie kam raha hun ab" 

Translation : The journey from Patna to Delhi has been a tough one, but after settling down which took almost 2 years, things have improved. Work seems fine and so do the people around, I aspire to be a manger at this very place, working hard towards the same

"If I talk too much I'll become the captain of Delhi. So I prefer to keep silent."

"Life as an advocate doesnt give me much time to take out the kids. 

The entire Sunday is for them now and I always take them out. The mother is usually ill"
#HOND #HumansofNewDelhi

"About New Delhi?"

"Umm can't say much, I'm always just passing by. Hope to spend more time here sometime."

Yes it has been away for a while but its hard to stay away. 

Humans Of New Delhi is back with more stories of lives of complete strangers on the streets of New Delhi.  Stay Tune #HOND

" Yahan bahut aate hain Sahab. Kabhi dubara aie, hum yahi milenge."

Translation : Sir, many people visit this place. Do come again, you shall find me at the same spot.

"My grandfather established this shop in 1946 
 and my son is currently working with Anil Kapoor in Mumbai, I just bought him a camera same as yours."

Spotted at : Chandni Chowk

The Humans Of New Delhi Project is an effort to create a photographic census of the city of New Delhi, with an eye toward creating artistic portraits of strangers on the street. 
We hope that one day there will be a map of the whole world where you can click and see the people that live in each city.

status_message: In every few moments he would look at the Amar Jawan Jyoti behind him, with eyes full of pride.

His eyes were fixed on the water for a long time.

"I have come to Delhi to study. I live with my Brother's family"
"At first it was just a job but now this suit completes me and HE inspires me. I wish I could meet HIM."
If you are living in Sarita Vihar and still haven't met this guy then you are missing out on a prodigy

His son recently topped his class and aspires to join the army.

Taking dad's vision to the next level.
He gave me his son's email ID, I still have to email him this picture.

"It took time to get used to this city, but the warmth, the culture, the life here and the people made it home. "

Spotted at Cannaught Place

I met him at the heart of New Delhi. 

Curious at first, he came around quite well sharing his travel experiences and the reason why he loves his unusual hairdo.

He didn't let me click him first cause he thought I was from the Press.

The fear of the cops sweeping them out of business still looms large

From Rangoon, living in Rishikesh, finding our purpose of existence in this urban jungle

Spotted in Chandi Chowk
